Mujra is a dance form that takes some elements from the native classical Kathak & Music including thumris and ghazals.  It was traditionally perfomed in mehfils during the Mughal period.  In present day popular culture , Mujra is taught with more dance choreography to make the female dancer more fluent in her moves and to be more artistic and feminine. Can we confess? We even followed @ashanegi she isn’t just an actor, but the woman who brought Roshni to life and asked her the one question that’s been haunting everyone.
